==Chart performance==
[[File:DanielPowterJan09.jpg|thumb|left|upright=0.60|"SOS" displaced [[Daniel Powter]]"s (''pictured'') "[[Bad Day (Daniel Powter song)|Bad Day]]" from the number one position on the US ''[[Billboard charts|Billboard]]'' [[Billboard Hot 100|Hot 100]], which spent five consecutive weeks atop the chart. ]]
In the United States, "SOS" peaked at number one on the ''[[Billboard charts|Billboard]]'' [[Billboard Hot 100|Hot 100]] chart in the chart issue dated May 13, 2006, leaping 33 positions from the previous week,<ref name="SOSHot100Debut">{{cite news|last=Hope|first=Clover|url=http://www.billboard.com/news#/news/1002462812.story|title=Rihanna's 'SOS' Rockets To No. 1 On Hot 100|work=Billboard|publisher=Nielsen Business Media, Inc|date=2006-05-04|accessdate=2009-01-11}}</ref> and became the singer's first number one single on the Hot 100.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://idolator.com/5832011/rihanna-10th-1-single-sm|title=Which Of Rihanna<U+2019>s 10 #1 Singles Is Your Favorite?|publisher=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]. [[Buzz Media]]|accessdate=2012-01-06}}</ref> "SOS" experienced a surge in sales the week prior to reaching the summit of the chart, due to Def Jam holding off of releasing the song to digital outlets before the release of ''A Girl like Me''.<ref name="SOSHot100Debut"/> The song displaced [[Daniel Powter]]"s "[[Bad Day (Daniel Powter song)|Bad Day]]" from number one, which had spent the previous five weeks atop the chart.<ref name="SOSHot100Debut"/> "SOS" stayed atop the Hot 100 for a further two weeks, spending three consecutive weeks at number one.<ref name="SOSHot100Week2">{{cite news|last=Hope|first=Clover|url=http://www.billboard.com/news#/news/1002501219.story|title=Rihanna Stays Strong On Hot 100|work=Billboard|publisher=Nielsen Business Media, Inc|date=2006-05-11|accessdate=2009-01-11}}</ref><ref name="SOSHot100Week3">{{cite news|last=Hope|first=Clover|url=http://www.billboard.com/news#/news/1002538614.story|title=Rihanna's 'SOS' Signals 3rd Week At No. 1|work=Billboard|publisher=Nielsen Business Media, Inc|date=2006-05-18|accessdate=2009-01-11}}</ref> "SOS" peaked at number one on the US [[Hot Dance Club Songs]] and [[Mainstream Top 40 (Pop Songs)|Pop Songs]] charts, respectively.<ref name="USDance">{{cite news|url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/rihanna/chart-history/658897#/artist/rihanna/chart-history/658897?f=359&g=Singles|title=Rihanna Chart History - Hot Dance Club Songs|work=Billboard|publisher=Prometheus Global Media|accessdate=2012-01-04}}</ref><ref name="USPop">{{cite news|url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/rihanna/chart-history/658897#/artist/rihanna/chart-history/658897?f=381&g=Singles|title=Rihanna Chart History - Pop Songs|work=Billboard|publisher=Prometheus Global Media|accessdate=2012-01-04}}</ref> The song also peaked at number seven on the [[Rhythmic contemporary|Radio Songs]] chart and peaked at number 40 on the [[Adult Contemporary (chart)|Adult Contemporary]] chart.<ref name="USRadio">{{cite news|url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/rihanna/chart-history/658897#/artist/rihanna/chart-history/658897?f=350&g=Singles|title=Rihanna Chart History - Radio Songs|work=Billboard|publisher=Prometheus Global Media|accessdate=2012-01-04}}</ref><ref name="USAdult">{{cite news|url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/rihanna/chart-history/658897#/artist/rihanna/chart-history/658897?f=341&g=Singles|title=Rihanna Chart History - Adult Contemporary|work=Billboard|publisher=Prometheus Global Media|accessdate=2012-01-04}}</ref> On January 7, 2007, "SOS" was certified platinum by the [[Recording Industry Association of America]] (RIAA), denoting shipments of over 1,000,000 copies.<ref name="RIAA">{{cite web|url=http://riaa.com/goldandplatinumdata.php?content_selector=gold-platinum-searchable-database#|title=RIAA searchable database: Rihanna|publisher=[[Recording Industry Association of America]]|date=2007-10-26|accessdate=2011-10-01}}</ref>

In Europe, "SOS" achieved moderate chart success in multiple territories. In Belgium (Flanders),  the song debuted at number 18 on April 22, 2006, and peaked at number two in its fourth week charting.<ref name="Flanders">{{cite web|url=http://www.ultratop.be/nl/showitem.asp?interpret=Rihanna&titel=SOS&cat=s|title=Rihanna <U+2013> SOS (Song)|work=''ultratop.be''|publisher=Hung Median|accessdate=2012-01-05}}</ref> In Switzerland, "SOS" debuted and peaked at number three on May 21, 2006, and stayed inside the top-ten of that countries singles chart for the following nine weeks.<ref name="Switzerland">{{cite web|url=http://hitparade.ch/showitem.asp?interpret=Rihanna&titel=SOS&cat=s|title=Rihanna <U+2013> SOS (Song)|work=''hitparade.ch''|publisher=Hung Median|accessdate=2012-01-05|language=German}}</ref> In Finland, the song spent two weeks on the countries singles chart; "SOS" debuted and peaked at number two on April 24, 2006, and fell to number 14 to following week.<ref name="Finland">{{cite web|url=http://finnishcharts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Rihanna&titel=SOS&cat=s|title=Rihanna <U+2013> SOS (Song)|work=''finnishcharts.com''|publisher=Hung Median|accessdate=2012-01-05}}</ref> In Norway, "SOS" debuted at number 16 on April 17, 2006, and peaked at number three in its third week charting.<ref name="Norway">{{cite web|url=http://norwegiancharts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Rihanna&titel=SOS&cat=s|title=Rihanna <U+2013> SOS (Song)|work=''norwegiancharts.com''|publisher=Hung Median|accessdate=2012-01-05}}</ref> Elsewhere, the song attained top-five positions on the singles charts of Austria and Belgium (Wallonia), peaking at numbers four and five, respectively.<ref name="Austria">{{cite web|url=http://austriancharts.at/showitem.asp?interpret=Rihanna&titel=SOS&cat=s|title=Rihanna <U+2013> SOS (Song)|work=''austriancharts.at''|publisher=Hung Median|accessdate=2012-01-05}}</ref><ref name="Wallonia">{{cite web|url=http://www.ultratop.be/fr/showitem.asp?interpret=Rihanna&titel=SOS&cat=s|title=Rihanna <U+2013> SOS (Song)|work=''ultratop.be''|publisher=Hung Median|accessdate=2012-01-05}}</ref> " SOS" attained top-ten positions in The Netherlands and Italy, peaking at numbers six and seven, respectively.<ref name="Netherlands">{{cite web|url=http://dutchcharts.nl/showitem.asp?interpret=Rihanna&titel=SOS&cat=s|title=Rihanna <U+2013> SOS (Song)|work=''dutchcharts.nl''|publisher=Hung Median|accessdate=2011-12-25}}</ref><ref name="Italy">{{cite web|url=http://italiancharts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Rihanna&titel=SOS&cat=s|title=Rihanna <U+2013> SOS (Song)|work=''italiancharts.com''|publisher=Hung Median|accessdate=2011-12-26}}</ref> The song failed to chart within the top-ten in France and Sweden, peaking at number 12 on both countries singles charts.<ref name="France">{{cite web|url=http://lescharts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Rihanna&titel=SOS&cat=s|title=Rihanna <U+2013> SOS (Song)|work=''lesharts.com''|publisher=Hung Median|accessdate=2011-12-26|language=French}}</ref><ref name="Sweden">{{cite web|url=http://swedishcharts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Rihanna&titel=SOS&cat=s|title=Rihanna <U+2013> SOS (Song)|work=''swedishcharts.com''|publisher=Hung Median|accessdate=2011-12-26}}</ref>

In the United Kingdom, "SOS" debuted at number five on April 22, 2006.<ref name="UKDebut">{{cite web|url=http://www.theofficialcharts.com/archive-chart/_/1/2006-04-22/|title=2006 Top 40 Official UK Singles Archive 22nd April 2006|publisher=[[The Official Charts Company]]|date=2006-04-22|accessdate=2012-01-05}}</ref> The following week, the song rose to number two, being held off of the number one position by [[Gnarls Barkley]]'s "[[Crazy (Gnarls Barkley song)|Crazy]]".<ref name="UK2ndWeek">{{cite web|url=http://www.theofficialcharts.com/archive-chart/_/1/2006-04-29/|title=2006 Top 40 Official UK Singles Archive 29th April 2006|publisher=The Official Charts Company|date=2006-04-29|accessdate=2012-01-05}}</ref> In its third week charting, both "SOS" and "Crazy" retained their respective chart positions.<ref name="UK3rdWeek">{{cite web|url=http://www.theofficialcharts.com/archive-chart/_/1/2006-05-06/|title=2006 Top 40 Official UK Singles Archive 6th May 2006|publisher=The Official Charts Company|date=2006-05-06|accessdate=2012-01-05}}</ref> Over the following weeks, "SOS" began to descend down the top-ten of the chart, falling to number five for two weeks, whilst "Crazy" retained its number one position.<ref name="UK4thWeek">{{cite web|url=http://www.theofficialcharts.com/archive-chart/_/1/2006-05-13/|title=2006 Top 40 Official UK Singles Archive 13th May 2006|publisher=The Official Charts Company|date=2006-05-13|accessdate=2012-01-05}}</ref><ref name="UK5thWeek">{{cite web|url=http://www.theofficialcharts.com/archive-chart/_/1/2006-05-20/|title=2006 Top 40 Official UK Singles Archive 20th May 2006|publisher=The Official Charts Company|date=2006-05-20|accessdate=2012-01-05}}</ref> In Australia, "SOS" debuted at number one on April 30, 2006, a position it held for eight consecutive weeks.<ref name="Australia">{{cite web|url=http://australian-charts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Rihanna&titel=SOS&cat=s|title=Rihanna <U+2013> SOS (Song)|work=''australian-charts.com''|publisher=Hung Median|accessdate=2012-01-05}}</ref> In New Zealand, the song debuted at number 37 on April 10, 2006, and spent the following five weeks fluctuating in the lower region of the top-40 singles.<ref name="NZ">{{cite web|url=http://charts.org.nz/showitem.asp?interpret=Rihanna&titel=SOS&cat=s|title=Rihanna <U+2013> SOS (Song)|work=''charts.org.nz''|publisher=Hung Median|accessdate=2012-01-05}}</ref> In its seventh week charting, the song leaped to a peak of number three for two weeks.<ref name="NZ"/>

==Music videos==
"SOS" received three separate treatments for the music video, each serving a different purpose. In addition to the official music video, another version was shot as part of a promotional campaign for lingerie brand [[Agent Provocateur (lingerie)|Agent Provocateur]], whilst another was shot for a [[Nike, Inc.|Nike]] campaign.<ref name="3Versions">{{cite web|url=http://blog.music.aol.com/2010/08/24/top-rihanna-videos/|title=Top 10 Rihanna Videos|publisher=[[AOL]]|accessdate=2012-01-05}}</ref> The official music video and Nike versions were directed by [[Chris Applebaum]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://watch.muchmusic.com/top-artists/rihanna/clip74333#clip74333|title=Rihanna <U+2013> S.O.S. (Rescue Me) |publisher=[[MuchMusic]]. [[CTVglobemedia]]|accessdate=2012-01-05}}</ref> who later directed the music video for "[[Umbrella (song)|Umbrella]]" (''[[Good Girl Gone Bad]]'', 2007).<ref>{{cite web|last=Rodriguez|first=Jayson|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1568860/20070904/rihanna.jhtml|title=Rihanna's 'Umbrella' Clip was Paint By Numbers|publisher=MTV. Viacom|date=2007-09-05|accessdate=2012-01-05}}</ref>

===Official music video===
The video begins with Rihanna singing the hook while wearing a [[D<U+00E9>colletage|low cut]] cut green dress and dancing in front tropical plants on a beach, whilst singing the [[Hook (music)|hook]]. [[Key light|Key lighting]] is used to place emphasis on Rihanna, whilst the backdrop remains virtually dark and unseeable. For the first [[Verse_(music)#Verse|verse]], Rihanna is featured dancing against a plain grey background, wearing a white top and silver glitter mini-skirt, whilst flirtatiously dancing with the male dancer. Halfway through the verse, another scene is introduced, with Rihanna wearing a pink dress in a mirrored room, showing multiple reflections of the singer from different angles. For the first [[Verse_(music)#Chorus|chorus]], Rihanna is mainly featured wearing the green dress on the beach, but a new scene of Rihanna wearing black lace is introduced toward the end of the chorus, where she, as well as four male dancers, perform a choreographed dance routine. Scenes of Rihanna in the mirrored room are intercut with the previous scene for the duration of the chorus. For the second verse, a further scene of Rihanna is depicted, this time featuring the scenes performing a dance routine with a group of female dancers, in the same setting as the one at the start of the video. For the second chorus, another scene of the singer sitting on a chair whilst listening to music is shown. For the remainder of the video, including the [[Verse_(music)#Bridge|bridge]] and final chorus, all scenes featured in the video are intercut with one and other, displaying a total of five different scenes and settings.

===Nike version===
The video begins with a [[Long shot|long shot]] of a group of dancers who have just finished rehearsing a dance routine. As the dancers walk out of view, Rihanna walks onto the middle of the floor, where the singer turns, and faces the camera, and closes her eyes. Standing still, Rihanna begins to click her fingers, whereby the screen begins to cut between a scene of Rihanna, who is noticeably in a different setting, and black [[Dissolve (filmmaking)|fades]]. As the song's audio begins to play, it becomes apparent that the setting has changed from a rehearsal studio into a nightclub, which Rihanna in the centre. The scene is fairly dark with different colour lights projected into different areas of the nightclub, as dancers infiltrate the dance floor surrounding Rihanna. This scene is used for the first verse-chorus-verse part of the song, but changes to a scene of Rihanna, accompanied by several dancers, situated in a gym locker room for the second chorus. For the bridge, the scene changes back to Rihanna in the nightclub, but this time in a different change of attire. This scene is used for the final chorus. The video ends with a [[Close-up|close-up]] of Rihanna in the nightclub standing still as the audio finishes, where she closes her eyes, which prompts the scene to change back to Rihanna in the middle of the rehearsal studio from the beginning of the video, to which she walks out of view of the camera.

